main event: A civilian reported an unidentified aerial phenomenon in Dayton, Ohio on September 18, 1969.
interesting points: The object was described as a bright, star-like object as bright as the star Capella.
The object remained in approximately the same position as the star Capella during the sighting.
The report indicates the observer likely saw the star Capella, which was at an altitude of 10 degrees and an azimuth of 240 degrees at the time of the sighting.
The report concludes the sighting was a probable misidentification of the star Capella.
The report includes a detailed summary and analysis of the sighting.
